22/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's (RS) ruling party, the Union of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), has nominated Rajko Kuzmanovic for president. 
The election is scheduled for December 9th, following the death last month of incumbent Milan Jelic. 
On Friday (October 19th), SNSD leader Milorad Dodik said he hopes Kuzmanovic's candidacy would garner broad support. 
Both the Socialist Party and the Democratic People's Union have said they will back Kuzmanovic, the current chairman of the RS Academy of Science. 
The entity's main opposition party, the Serb Democratic Party, is nominating parliament member Ognjien Tadic for president. 
(Nezavisne Novine - 20/10/07; RTRS, PBS - 19/10/07)
